Heat your #oven{} to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp} for the pasta. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Halve the @green pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded) and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 3cm sized chunks. Coarsely grate the @carrot{1}(coarsely grated, no need to peel). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large deep #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the @lamb mince{200%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Break it up with a #wooden spoon{} as it cooks. Add the onion, carrot and pepper and continue to cook until the veggies are slightly softened, ~{5%minutes}.

Add the garlic and @Mexican style spice mix{Mexican Spice} (add less if you don't like heat!) and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}. Add the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1}(can), @red wine stock paste{28%g} and @water for the sauce{150%ml}. Season with salt and @pepper{pinch}, stir well to dissolve the stock pot and simmer until thick and tomatoey, ~{10-12%minutes}. While the sauce simmers, add the @penne pasta{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, mix the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} with the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Season with salt and pepper and mix well.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain well and mix with the Mexican beef. Transfer to a #baking dish{}, sprinkle over the cheesy breadcrumbs and bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown on top, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Leave the pasta bake to stand for a couple of minutes then divide between plates and enjoy!

> Step 2 MOD: If you've chosen to get lamb mince instead of beef mince, simply cook the lamb in the same way the recipe tells you to cook the beef above, and follow the steps as normal.